The perfect probably did not exist in Proto-Akkadian, and was developed in historical times under the influence of Sumerian (especially to cover part of expressive range of Sum. prefix ba-). Choice of infixed -t- was probably influenced, as suggested by Gelb, by the superlative value of the t-infixad stems.
